**5. Apply the Law of Cosines to find $\angle PAM$**

In triangle $PAM$, we have $PA = 630$, $AM = 200$, and $PM = 200\sqrt{3}$ (the circumradius).  Applying the Law of Cosines to find $\cos \angle PAM$:

\begin{align*}
630^2 &= 200^2 + (200\sqrt{3})^2 - 2 \cdot 200 \cdot 200\sqrt{3} \cos \angle PAM \\
\Rightarrow \cos \angle PAM &= \frac{200^2 + (200\sqrt{3})^2 - 630^2}{2 \cdot 200 \cdot 200\sqrt{3}} \\
&= \frac{40000 + 120000 - 396900}{80000\sqrt{3}} \\
