In triangle $PMD$, we know $\angle PAM = \angle PMD$ (since $MD \perp AP$).  Also, $\sin \angle PAM = \sqrt{1 - \cos^2 \angle PAM} = \sqrt{1 - \left( -\frac{2369}{80\sqrt{3}} \right)^2} = \frac{\sqrt{1761}}{80\sqrt{3}}$.

