\[[I_BI_CE_BE_C] = [I_BI_CA] + [E_BE_CA] = (1 + k^2) [I_BI_CA] = 37 [I_BI_CA].\]Since $[I_BI_CE_BE_C] = 7,$ we have $[I_BI_CA] = \frac{7}{37}.$

Also, $[I_BI_CA] = \frac{1}{2} \cdot I_BI_C \cdot I_A \cdot \sin \angle I_BI_CA = \frac{1}{2} \cdot 1 \cdot I_A \cdot \sin \frac{1}{2} \angle BAC = \frac{1}{2} I_A \sin \frac{1}{2} \angle BAC.$  Then
\[\frac{7}{37} = \frac{1}{2} I_A \sin \frac{1}{2} \angle BAC.\]Similarly,
\[\frac{7}{37} = \frac{1}{2} E_A \sin \frac{1}{2} \angle BAC.\]Hence, $I_A = E_A.$

Since $I_A$ and $E_A$ are the incenter and excenter of triangle $ABD,$ respectively, $I_A$ is the midpoint of segment $DE_A.$  Hence, $DE_A = 2I_A = 2E_A.$

