\[\frac{AI_B \cdot AI_C}{\sin^2 \alpha} = \frac{AB \cdot AC}{\sin (\angle ABI_B) \sin (\angle ACI_C)}.\]Since $AI_B \cdot AI_C = I_B I_C = 1$, we have
\[\frac{1}{\sin^2 \alpha} = \frac{AB \cdot AC}{\sin (\angle ABI_B) \sin (\angle ACI_C)}.\]Similarly,
\[\frac{1}{\sin^2 \beta} = \frac{AB \cdot AC}{\sin (\angle ABE_B) \sin (\angle ACE_C)}.\]

